This presidential memorandum, issued on November 3, 2018, delegates authority to the Secretary of State regarding Condition 23 of the United States Senate's Resolution of Advice and Consent to Ratification of the Chemical Weapons Convention. The Secretary of State, in coordination with other departments and agencies, is given the authority to carry out the functions assigned to the President in relation to this condition. The memorandum also directs the publication of this document in the Federal Register.